pond with:\n`{\"ok\": false, \"decision\": \"block\", \"reason\": \"[IMMEDIATE: /reflect]\\n\\n教訓が見つかりましたが、仕組み化されていません。まず振り返り（/reflect）を実行してから、フック/CI/ツールで再発防止の仕組みを作成してください。\"}`\n\n## Decision Rules\n- If the JSON context contains `\"stop_hook_active\": true`, respond with `{\"ok\": true, \"decision\": \"approve\"}` to prevent infinite loops\n- If there are CRITICAL unfinished tasks or obvious errors, respond with `{\"ok\": false, \"decision\": \"block\", \"reason\": \"[specific action needed]\"}`\n- If problems were discovered but not documented as Issues, BLOCK (see Issue Documentation Check above)\n- If lessons were learned but not systematized, BLOCK (see Systematization Check above)\n- If the main task is substantially complete, respond with `{\"ok\": true, \"decision\": \"approve\", \"systemMessage\": \"✅ 振り返り完了\"}`\n\n## Important\n- Do NOT block for minor improvements or nice-to-haves\n- Only block for critical incomplete work\n- ALWAYS block if problems discovered but not documented as Issues\n- ALWAYS block if lessons learned were not systematized\n- Be specific in the reason field about what needs to be done\n- The goal is quality assurance, not perfectionism\n\nRespond with valid JSON only.",
